19#include "QRErrorCorrectionLevel.h"
20
21#include <cstdint>
22
23namespace ZXing {
24namespace QRCode {
25
26/**
27* <p>Encapsulates a QR Code's format information, including the data mask used and
28* error correction level.</p>
29*
30* @author Sean Owen
31* @see DataMask
32* @see ErrorCorrectionLevel
33*/
34class FormatInformation
35{
36public:
37 FormatInformation() = default;
38
39 static FormatInformation DecodeFormatInformation(int maskedFormatInfo1, int maskedFormatInfo2);
40
41 ErrorCorrectionLevel errorCorrectionLevel() const {
42 return _errorCorrectionLevel;
43 }
44
45 uint8_t dataMask() const {
46 return _dataMask;
47 }
48
49 bool isValid() const { return _errorCorrectionLevel != ErrorCorrectionLevel::Invalid; }
50
51 bool operator==(const FormatInformation& other) const {
52 return _dataMask == other._dataMask && _errorCorrectionLevel == other._errorCorrectionLevel;
53 }
54
55private:
56 ErrorCorrectionLevel _errorCorrectionLevel = ErrorCorrectionLevel::Invalid;
57 uint8_t _dataMask = 0;
58
59 FormatInformation(int formatInfo);
60
61 static FormatInformation DoDecodeFormatInformation(int maskedFormatInfo1, int maskedFormatInfo2);
62};
63
64} // QRCode
65} // ZXing
